		"description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">When you select this archetype at 1st level, you begin to learn how to manipulate the powers and energies of death.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>You learn the <em>spare the dying</em> cantrip, which does not count against your number of cantrips known.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Choose one of the following:</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><s><strong>Death Curse</strong></s></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><strong>Mortal Defiance</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">You can cast <em>spare the dying</em> as a bonus action. In addition, when you are reduced to 0 hit points as a reaction you may cast spare the dying on yourself.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">When you cast spare the dying on another creature that is actually dying, you regain hit points equal to 1d8 + you Charisma modifier.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">You have advantage on saving throws against poison and disease.</p>",
